VALUES
  (150, 'Cornwall Council business rates (direct debit)', '^DIRECT DEBIT.*CORNWALL COUNCIL', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'tax_payment', 0.93, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; Recurring monthly direct debits to Cornwall Council on the main trading account (acct 15), two DD refs (802858250 fixed ~£101, 80285826X variable ~£505-£777) running 2021-2026 — classic business-rates instalment pattern for the pub premises. Existing rule 45 (''^CORNWALL COUNCIL'', tax_payment) already covers this exact category but is anchored to the start of t'),
  (151, 'Sian Libby Mills recurring personal payment', '^SIAN LIBBY MILLS , (FP [0-9]|CHILD MAINTENANCE , VIA ONLINE)', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[3]::int[], 'personal_spend', 0.88, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified REFINED; 50 of 53 rows on Jo''s personal account (acct 6, entity 3) are an identical recurring monthly standing-order-style payment of exactly -£650.00 (2 more at the prior rate of -£540.28) running continuously 2021-12 through 2026-05, one row explicitly tagged ''CHILD MAINTENANCE''. This is a stable, single-purpose recurring personal outgoing on Jo''s own account — safe to'),
  (152, 'Dojo card-machine Direct Debit fee', '^Direct Debit DOJOUK PS32GC-GB', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'bank_fee', 0.90, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; All 25 needs_review rows matching ''DOJOUK PS32GC-GB'' are on account 15 (ATR Trading main), all Direct Debits, all negative, roughly monthly cadence 2024-01 to 2026-03, amounts £246-£1600. This is the merchant-service/card-terminal fee DD from Dojo (distinct from Dojo card-settlement credits, which are already covered by 3 existing rules requiring amount>0). Ze'),
  (153, 'Northcorn Linen supplier payment', 'NORTHCORN LINEN', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'supplier_payment', 0.85, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; Decisive sub-pattern inside the heterogeneous ''CONTRACT'' cluster: 5 needs_review rows all on account 15, all negative, all naming ''NORTHCORN LINEN'' as the payee inside the standard ''CONTRACT, VIA (ONLINE|MOBILE) - PYMT...MALTHOUSE MOBILE/ONLINE'' NatWest narrative. This is a linen-hire supplier for the pub (consistent with Malthouse trade-supplier conventions e'),
  (154, 'Jolyon Sandercock Cleeton rent transfer (ONLINE-PYMTB variant)', 'JOLYON SANDERCOCK CLEETON RENT', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'transfer_uncategorised', 0.92, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; Sub-pattern inside the ''JOLYON SANDERCOCK'' cluster. 6 byte-for-byte-equivalent sibling rows (same account 15, same -£1000.00, same ''JOLYON SANDERCOCK ... Cleeton rent'' text, monthly-ish cadence through 2024) already sit at transfer_uncategorised via the existing ''Internal Mobile Xfer'' rule (priority 40, matches literal ''VIA MOBILE''). These 3 needs_review rows '),
  (155, 'Pennon Water DD - ATR Trading (acct 15)', 'PENNON WATER SRVCS', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'direct_debit', 0.92, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; 22 negative rows on acct 15 (ATR Trading main current), all ''Direct Debit PENNON WATER SRVCS 5006167601...'' -- a business water-rates DD, statement reference number confirmed constant across all rows. Entity 1 + negative sign cleanly isolates this account from the entity-1 Cap on Tap card rows (which are positive, handled separately below), so no overlap.'),
  (156, 'Pennon Water - Cap on Tap card (acct 16)', 'PENNON WATER.*Card Ending', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'supplier_payment', 0.90, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; Card-account sign trap: acct 16 (Cap on Tap business credit card) inverts sign vs bank accounts, so positive = spend. 2 rows ''PENNON WATER SERVICES - EXETER - Card Ending: ...'', consistent with the existing convention on this account (297 already-categorised supplier_payment rows are all positive, £3.44-£22,719.63 range, so these £2,561/£2,839 charges fit squa'),
  (157, 'Pennon Water DD - personal (acct 6)', 'PENNON WATER', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[3]::int[], 'direct_debit', 0.85, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; 19 negative rows on acct 6 (Jo personal main current), mix of plain ''PENNON WATER SRVCS'' and card-coded forms (''9897 10SEP20 , PENNON WATER , SERVICES , EXETER GB'') -- all the same personal water-rates biller, recurring quarterly-ish cadence, amounts £282-£1,275. Matches the account''s dominant existing convention (1,050 rows already categorised direct_debit). '),
  (158, 'Watson Fuels - Cap on Tap card (acct 16)', 'WATSON FUELS', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'supplier_payment', 0.92, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; 26 rows, all on acct 16 (Cap on Tap), all positive (£5.59-£932.19) -- fuel supplier, card-sign trap (positive=spend). Same ''T''/''B'' branch-code and 0000000-account variants all resolve to the same supplier. Matches the account''s established supplier_payment convention.'),
  (159, 'Amazon.co.uk - Cap on Tap card (acct 16)', '^AMAZON\.CO\.UK -', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'supplier_payment', 0.88, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; 220 rows, all on acct 16, all positive (£3.49-£784.99) -- prefix-anchored to ''AMAZON.CO.UK - <acct number>'' which is a distinct, consistently-formatted narrative from other Amazon variants on this same card (AMAZON*, AMZNMktplace, AMZNBusiness -- those include the 6 negative/refund rows and were deliberately left out by the anchor). Card-sign trap: positive=sp'),
  (160, 'NEST pension DD - broadened comma format (acct 15)', 'NEST[, ]*IT000005336182', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'wages', 0.85, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified REFINED; Existing rule id=97 (priority 207) uses description_re=''NEST IT'' with amount<0/entity=1 and already covers most NEST pension DDs -- but it requires the literal substring ''NEST IT'' with no separator, while these 28 missed rows are formatted ''NEST , IT000005336182'' (comma-space between NEST and the account reference), so the existing regex never matches. All 28 ro'),
  (161, 'NEST pension refund credit (acct 15)', 'Automated Credit NEST PENSION PMT', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'refund', 0.70, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; 2 small positive credits (£14.42, £38.92) on acct 15 labelled ''Automated Credit NEST PENSION PMT P<ref>'' -- the pension provider crediting back an overpayment/correction. Clean, distinct format from the DD debits, low value, decisive pattern.'),
  (162, 'simmons_ca_recurring_credit_income_rent', 'SIMMONS C A', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[3]::int[], 'income_rent', 0.75, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; 25 rows, all account 6 (Jo personal, entity 3), all positive Faster Payments credits, £400/mo (one early £1600 catch-up) from 2023-07 to 2025-10 with reference ''BILL''. Matches the existing house convention seen in rule id=102 (priority 212): a list of named individuals paying recurring amounts into account 6 is already categorised income_rent (tenant/lodger bi'),
  (163, 'roxanne_gunner_salutations_rent', 'ROXANNE GUNNER', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[3]::int[], 'income_rent', 0.92, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; 8 rows, all account 6 (entity 3), all £1300 Faster Payment credits monthly Jul-2025 to Mar-2026, reference ''3 SALUTATIONS'' — Salutations is a known Jo-personal property per project_properties_mortgages. This is decisive rental income from a named tenant at a specific address, directly analogous to the existing named-tenant income_rent rules (id=102/103/106). N'),
  (164, 'amznmktplace_captontap_card16_supplier_payment', 'AMZNMKTPLACE.*CARD ENDING', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'supplier_payment', 0.85, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; This specific cluster head (''AMZNMKTPLACE - AMAZON.CO.UK - CARD ENDING:'') is exactly the account-16 Cap on Tap business-card narrative format (226 rows, all bank_account_id=16, entity_id=1). Account 16 already has 297 non-needs_review rows overwhelmingly categorised supplier_payment via near-identical vendor+''CARD ENDING'' rules (ids 82-85, 101) with amount_op '),
