  (166, 'fdms_old_malthouse_card_settlement', 'ONLINE - PYMT MOBILE/ONLINE THE OLD MALTHOUSE , FDMS', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'card_settlement', 0.80, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified REFINED; 3 rows, all account 15 (entity 1), Aug 2020, positive amounts, exact phrase ''VIA/PYMT MOBILE/ONLINE THE OLD MALTHOUSE , FDMS'' — old-style (pre-Dojo-rebrand) card machine settlement narrative into the pub''s main account. Existing rule id=69 (card_settlement, ''FDEL FASTER PAYMEN|FDMS 510878762'', amount>0, entity 1) is the closest analog but misses these because th'),
  (167, 'BT GROUP direct debit (ARTL telecom)', 'BT GROUP', NULL, '<', 0, NULL, 'direct_debit', 0.90, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified REFINED; 58 rows, single account (15 = Atlantic Road Trading/pub), all debits, monthly recurring amounts £28-£603 over 2023-07 to 2026-03, narrative consistently ''Direct Debit BT GROUP PLC GP...'' with two separate DD reference series (...858920 and ...494218) — classic split phone/broadband billing. No existing rule covers BT GROUP; matches the established convention use'),
  (168, 'Arval UK Ltd vehicle lease DD (ARTL)', 'ARVAL UK LTD AT', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'direct_debit', 0.85, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; 22 rows, single account (15 = ARTL/pub), all debits, one larger opening payment (-£2414.56, likely contract initiation + first instalment) followed by 21 near-identical monthly payments of -£268.28 (one month -£283.28) referencing the same contract ''AT9276'', from 2024-03 to 2025-12. Arval UK is a well-known commercial vehicle-leasing company — this is the pub'''),
  (169, 'DesignMyNight.com subscription DD (ARTL, debits only)', 'DESIGNMYNIGHT\.COM', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'direct_debit', 0.85, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; 41 rows, single account (15 = ARTL/pub), all debits, monthly recurring £130-£581 from 2022-09 to 2026-05, narrative ''Direct Debit DESIGNMYNIGHT.COM 1101140'' (originally routed via Paymentsense/Dojo DD collection, later a plain DD). This is the pub''s booking-platform SaaS subscription fee, distinct from the existing rule 203 (card_settlement, ''ACCESS PAYSUITE..'),
  (170, 'Dojo/PaymentSense DD fee (DOJOUK PSXKKA)', 'DOJOUK PSXKKA', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'direct_debit', 0.92, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; Distinct from the existing ''Dojo card settlement'' rules (id 4, priority 20; id 42, priority 45), which only match amount>0 (incoming settlement credits). These are outgoing Direct Debit collections by ''DOJOUK PSXKKA-GB<ref>'' on account 15 (Atlantic Road Trading) — Dojo/PaymentSense''s own recurring merchant-service/terminal fee collection, separate legal entity'),
  (171, 'GoCardless — Clearbrew DD (Direct Debit prefix variant)', 'CLEARBREW', NULL, '<', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'direct_debit', 0.95, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; Existing rule 37 (priority 45, ^GOCARDLESS) already classifies GoCardless-collected direct debits as direct_debit, and is proven correct for this exact vendor — 4 CLEARBREW rows already carry category=direct_debit where the description happens to start with the bare token ''GOCARDLESS , CLEARBREW-Z62AYBH5'' (2026 statement format). The needs_review rows are the '),
