  (189, 'Named trade suppliers II — Cap On Tap card purchases (hardware/fuel/building)', '(THE HARDWARE SHOP|WATSON FUELS|TRAVIS PERKINS|TOOLSTATION|TOPPS TILES|WICKES).*CARD ENDING', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'supplier_payment', 0.90, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; Extends the existing rule-211 named-supplier list (same category, same account, same ''CARD ENDING'' anchor, same amount>0/entity 1 constraints) with six more clearly building/hardware/fuel trade suppliers seen repeatedly on the Cap On Tap card. 96 rows, £18,087.22. One negative Travis Perkins tool-hire refund row is deliberately excluded via amount>0.'),
  (190, 'ARE personal-property rent — named tenants (Lautier/Fenech, Hartley Home Care, G', '(LAUTIER|HARTLEY HOME CARE|GOODYER)', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[2]::int[], 'income_rent', 0.93, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; Matches the style of existing rule 212 (named-tenant surname → income_rent). Account 5 (ARE, entity 2) only, 49 rows total across three tenants: LAUTIER C A ref ''LAUTIER/FENECH'' (34 rows, consistent £550-£600/mo), HARTLEY HOME CARE explicitly tagged ''FLAT A LANGHOLME'' (11 rows, exact £750/mo — Langholme is a known ARE property per memory), and GOODYER M J expl'),
  (191, 'South West Water DD', '^SOUTH WEST WATER( |$)', NULL, '<', 0, NULL, 'direct_debit', 0.92, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; No existing rule. Household water DD across accounts 5, 6, and 10, all negative, 9 rows, £3801.90. Deliberately excludes the single outlier row ''SOUTH WEST WATER LTD EXETER'' (+£3766.08 on personal Mastercard acct 12 — different description format and a one-off card-style credit) via the anchored end-of-token match and separate amount>0 exclusion.'),
  (192, 'Reserve account interest credit (prefix/format variant)', 'INTEREST.*GRS 48885525', NULL, '>', 0, ARRAY[1]::int[], 'interest_credit', 0.95, 'panel 2026-07-10, verified CONFIRMED; Existing rule 10 is anchored to the exact format ''^[0-9]{1,2}[A-Z]{3} GRS [0-9]+$'' and misses rows where the feed adds ''TRANSACTION XFER INTEREST'', ''Interest'', or trailing ''£ £'' text around the same GRS reference. Account 20 only, 58 of the account''s 59 needs_review rows (the 59th is a one-off -£5000 director drawdown, deliberately excluded and left as needs_r')
